INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('24061', '4', '2015-08-31 20:11:41', '2015-08-31 20:11:41', '<strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Day 1</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Bienvenidos a Costa Rica ! Transporte con aire acondicionado al Hotel Presidente en San José.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>1 Noche Los alojamiento en el hotel presidente (o similar ) en 1 habitación estándar con desayuno incluido.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Hotel Presidente es un refugio urbano contemporáneo en el corazón del centro de San José. Con su ambiente vibrante, una decoración moderna y un gran servicio , el hotel de lujo de 4 estrellas, es el símbolo de la hospitalidad y el alma cultural de la capital de Costa Rica .</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>DAY 2</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Aire -acondicionado transporte desde San José a Hotel Tamarindo Diria Guanacaste</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>3 noches de alojamiento en el Hotel Tamarindo Diria</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Situado en el centro de la playa más famosa de Costa Rica , los tres pueblos que comprenden Tamarindo Diria Beach Resort - Sunset ( frente al mar ) , Laguna y Tropicana (al otro lado del Diria Grand Boulevard ) - evocan la auténtica Costa Rica . Tejiendo juntos para crear una experiencia singular y único son tres piscinas, una piscina de hidromasaje , bares, restaurantes, incluyendo un restaurante especializado en carnes .</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 3</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Kayak Tour - Yellow Fin Land Tour</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ven y únete a nosotros una aventura infantil disfrutando de las vistas de la bahía Espectacular flamenco, Isla Catalina e Isla Plata. Comience en las aguas planas de la vieja marina de salir al oeste limita con una línea de costa boscosa en la que se puede ver pelícanos marrones, piquero moreno y llegada cormorants.Upon neotropical en la isla se puede optar por continuar remando por la isla</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 4</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>ATV &amp; Canopy Tour - Yellow Fin Land Tour</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Garantía 100 % adrenalina !!! Llegamos a el tour de canopy a través de las montañas en un ATV . El tour de canopy está formada por cables , algunos hasta por 400 metros , usted también podrá apreciar el bosque desde el dosel de los árboles. Para finalizar este recorrido vamos a volver con nuestros vehículos todo terreno hasta el punto de partida.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>DAY 5</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Aire -condicionado transporte desde Hotel Tamarindo Diria Guanacaste al Hotel Arenal Manoa</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>3 noches de alojamiento en el Hotel Arenal Manoa</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Hotel Arenal Manoa es un hermoso lugar para descansar, relajarse y disfrutar de la maravillosa vista del Volcán Arenal . Rodeado de jardines, pastos y animales , nuestras habitaciones han sido diseñadas para que cada uno le ofrece una vista panorámica del volcán. Nuestros visitantes pueden tomar ventaja de nuestros amplios jardines de paseo y la meditación , así como las oportunidades para ver las operaciones diarias de una granja</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>DAY 6 </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Costa Rica Rafting Class 2-3 Whitewater &amp; Wildlife near Arenal</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>El rafting es una de las actividades más populares que hacer en Costa Rica y se ejecuta la lluvia o con sol casi todos los días del año . Ofrecemos la mejor Clase 2-3 de rafting cerca del Volcán Arenal en el hermoso río Balsa sólo 45 minutos fromyour hotel de La Fortuna .</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong><strong>El Río Balsa es el tour de rafting perfecto para principiantes , familias con niños , todos los amantes de la naturaleza , amantes del aire libre , y las personas que simplemente están buscando una aventura</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 7</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Stand Up Paddle en  Lake Arenal</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>el deporte más nuevo y más fresco de pádel en Costa Rica , a la derecha en la tranquila Lago Arenal, con hermosas vistas del Volcán Arenal colosal. Stand Up Paddling ve exactamente como suena: se pone de pie sobre una tabla grande , ancha súper boyante (similar a una tabla de surf ) y usar un largo remo para desplazarse a sí mismo a lo largo . Te sentirás como si estuvieras caminando sobre el agua !</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 8</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Transporte desde el hotel Manoa con Aire acondicionado  al Aeropuerto Internacional para tomar su vuelo </strong><strong>de regreso.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n[gravityform id=\"1\" title=\"true\" description=\"true\"]', '1 noche en San José - 3 noches en Tamarindo -3 noches en La Fortuna , Arenal(7 noches  /8 dias)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '1-noche-en-san-jose-3-noches-en-tamarindo-3-noches-en-la-fortuna-arenal7-noches-8-dias', '', '', '2015-09-01 19:01:53', '2015-09-01 19:01:53', '', '0', 'http://www.mmexperiencecr.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=24061', '0', 'product', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('24115', '4', '2015-09-08 17:09:24', '2015-09-08 17:09:24', '<span style=\"color: #333300;\">El complejo ofrece excelentes vistas del Arenal y Cerro Chato Volcanes, Fortuna City y la extensa Llanuras del Norte de Costa Rica. Inmerso en nuestra propiedad de 400 acres son de senderismo senderos privados de Cerro Chato ANC Park &amp; Jardines y el Corredor Biológico.</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Comodidades</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #333300;\">Desayuno gratuito.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Aire acondicionado.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Agua caliente.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Mini refrigerador.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Caja de Seguridad.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Spa.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Restaurante.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Bar.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Piscina</span>\n<span style=\"color: #333300;\">Jardines.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Rutas de senderismo.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Aparcamiento privado.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Acceso a Internet.</span><span style=\"color: #333300;\">Servicio de café.</span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Alojamiento</span></strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #333300;\">Mini refrigerador. Aire acondicionado. Agua Caliente.</span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Habitación estándar</span></strong>\n<span style=\"color: #333300;\">1 dormitorio. 1cama Queen + 1 Single.Alarm Reloj Caja de seguridad</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Cuarto superior</strong></span>\n1<span style=\"color: #333300;\"> dormitorio. 1cama king + 1 Double.sofa cama</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Villa Suite Familiar</strong></span>\n<span style=\"color: #333300;\">1 dormitorio. 2 king + 1 Sofá cama.</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Luna de miel Bungalow</strong></span>\n<span style=\"color: #333300;\">Capacidad para 4 personas en 1 habitación. 1cama king + 1 Sofa cama.cocina</span>\n\n[gravityform id=\"1\" title=\"true\" description=\"true\"]\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Hotel Green lagoon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22722-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-08 17:09:24', '2015-09-08 17:09:24', '', '22722', 'http://www.mmexperiencecr.com/2015/09/08/22722-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('24064', '4', '2015-08-31 20:31:49', '2015-08-31 20:31:49', '&nbsp;\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 1 </strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong> Welcome to Costa Rica! Air-conditioned Transportation to Hotel presidente   in San Jose.</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>1 Night Accommodations at Hotel president (or similar) in 1 standard Room with breakfast included.</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Hotel Presidente is a contemporary urban retreat in the heart of downtown San Jose. With its vibrant ambiance, modern décor and great service, our 4-star upscale hotel is the symbol of hospitality and the cultural soul of Costa Rica\'s capital city.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>DAY 2</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Air –conditioned transportation from San Jose to Hotel tamarindo diria Guanacaste </strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>3 Nights’ Accommodations at Hotel tamarindo Diria </strong></span>\n\n<strong> Located on the middle of the most famous beach in Costa Rica, the three villages comprising Tamarindo Diria Beach Resort – Sunset (Beachfront), Lagoon and Tropicana (across the Diria Grand Boulevard) – evoke the authentic Costa Rica. Weaving them together to create a singularly and unique experience are three pools, one whirlpool, bars, restaurants, including a steakhouse.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 3</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Kayak Tour - Yellow Fin Land Tour</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Come join us a paddling adventure enjoying the espectacular views of flamingo bay, Catalina island and Isla Plata. Start in the flat waters of the old marina heading out west bordering a forested coast line in which you can see brown pelicans, brown booby, magnificent frigatebierds and neotropical cormorants.Upon arrival at the island you can choose to continue paddling around the island or if you wish to snorkel there.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 4 </strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>ATV &amp; Canopy Tour - Yellow Fin Land Tour</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Guarantee 100 % adrenaline!!! We get to the canopy tour through the mountains on an ATV. The canopy tour is formed of cables, some as long as 400 meters, You will also be able to appreciate the forest from the canopy of the trees. To end this tour we will return with our ATVs to the departure point.</strong>\n<h3><strong>DAY 5</strong></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Air –conditioned transportation from Hotel tamarindo diria Guanacaste to hotel arenal </strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>3 Nights’ Accommodations at Hotel Arenal Manoa</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Arenal Manoa Hotel is a beautiful place to rest, relax and enjoy the marvelous view of Arenal Volcano. Surrounded by gardens, pastures and animals, our rooms have been designed so that each one offers you a panoramic view of the volcano. Our visitors can take advantage of our spacious gardens for walking and meditation as well as the opportunities to see the daily operations of a typical Costa Rican farm.</strong>\n<h3><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">DAY 6</span> </strong></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Costa Rica Rafting Class 2-3 Whitewater &amp; Wildlife near Arenal</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Rafting is one of the most-popular activities to do in Costa Rica and runs rain or shine just about EVERY day of the year. We offer the best Class 2-3 rafting near the Arenal Volcano on the beautiful Balsa River just 45 minutes fromyour La Fortuna hotel. </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong><strong>The Rio Balsa is the perfect rafting tour for first-timers, families with children, all nature lovers, outdoor enthusiasts, and people who are simply looking for a fun rafting adventure in Costa Rica!</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 7</strong></span></h3>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Stand Up Paddle on Lake Arenal</strong></span></h4>\n<strong>the newest and coolest paddle sport in Costa Rica, right on tranquil Lake Arenal with beautiful views of the colossal Arenal Volcano. Stand Up Paddling looks exactly as it sounds: you stand up on a large, wide, super buoyant board (similar to a surfboard) &amp; use a long paddle to move yourself along. You\'ll feel like you\'re walking on water! </strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 8</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #008080;\"><strong>Air-conditioned transportation from hotel Arenal Manoa to Int’l Airport to catch your flight home.</strong></span>\n\n[gravityform id=\"2\" title=\"true\" description=\"false\" ajax=\"true\"]', '1 night in San Jose – 3 nights In tamarindo -3 nights in La Fortuna, Arenal(7 nights /8 days )', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '24010-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-08-31 20:31:49', '2015-08-31 20:31:49', '', '24010', 'http://www.mmexperiencecr.com/2015/08/31/24010-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('24065', '4', '2015-08-31 20:34:24', '2015-08-31 20:34:24', '<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 1</strong></span></h3>\n<strong>Welcome to Costa Rica!!! You’ll be greeted at the airport by a private shuttle that will take you and your family to your hotel near Costa Rica’s most active volcano, “Arenal Volcano”. Along the way you’ll enjoy amazing scenery which is just a preview of what you and your family are about to experience.</strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>3 Nights’ Accommodations at Hotel arenal springs resort &amp; Spa (or similar)</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Arenal Springs Hotel is located just 5 miles away from the town of La Fortuna on the way towards the Arenal Volcano National Park.</strong><strong>Each distinctive Junior Suite comes with direct views to the beautiful Arenal Volcano.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 2</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Morning Pure Costa Rica Travel and Waterfall Rappel You will be picked up at your hotel 7:15 am and taken directly to the Pure Costa Rica Travel Headquarters just 5 minutes away.</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Come enjoy this fun tour with great guides, spectacular views and beautiful trails throughout! From children to adults and people with experience we are the specialists!</strong>\n\n<strong>4 Rappels (3 waterfalls and 1 rock wall) in a rainforest canyon,Hiking on beautiful trails in the canyon between rappels, Waterproof jackets.</strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Afternoon Arenal Volcano Hike and The baldi hot Springs Resort and Spa and dinner</strong></span>\n\n<strong>This  tour takes you to the active side of Arenal, where our naturalist guide will take you through rainforest trails for a nice and gentle hike to spot a big variety of diverse flora and fauna such as monkeys, toucans, wild turkeys, sloths, a big variety of birds and sometimes snakes.</strong>\n\n<strong>After your volcano hike your next stop is to The baldi hot springs resort and spa Here you will be treated to additional spectacular views of Volcano Arenal The baldi Resort &amp; Spa offers something for everyone and you’ll end the day with a delicious dinner. After your dinner and relaxing time in the hot springs, you’ll be driven back to your hotel.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 3</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Arenal – Hanging Bridges Tour</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Enjoy a beautiful hike through the tropical rainforest, walking for 2 hours on the Arenal Hanging Bridges. Wonderful panoramic views of Arenal Volcano and Lake Arenal.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 4</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>transportation from your hotel in arenal to jaco beach</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>4 Nights’ Accommodations at Hotel balcón del  Del Mar (or similar)</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Hotel Balcón del Mar is situated right on the ocean, in the most beautiful, colorful, quiet and save area of Jaco Beach. Our hotel offers various rooms, unparalleled ocean view, easy access for awesome surfing.</strong>\n\n<strong>The hotel is located in central pacific with many attractive spots to visit.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 5</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Jaco beach :</strong> <strong>The Explorer Waterfall Tour</strong></span>\n\n<strong>This is a tour that all waterfall and nature lovers must do when staying in Jaco beach. Experience the true meaning of the “Pura Vida” with our guides who will take you for a walk into the lush rain-forest near Jaco Beach, The majestic natural scenery will be overwhelming throughout the tour.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 6</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Jaco beach  Canopy Tour, Los Sueños</strong></span>\n\n<strong>The adventure starts on a 15 minute ride aboard our specially designed 40 passenger tractor. Once we arrive to the top of the mountain we then descend to the bottom via a series of zip lines, including 15 platforms and 14 cables with a total cable distance of 3.5 kilometer including the longest cable in the area of 2400 ft!!!! Join us on a wonderful nature walk for all ages; explore along with our tour guides the ancestral uses of medicinal plants, how vines grow, which tree barks are poisonous and how to survive by eating local plants.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 7</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #008080;\"><strong><strong><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Jaco beach rancho los tucanes Jungle River &amp; Crocodile Adventure   </span>   </strong>\n</strong></span>\n\n<strong>This crazy adrenaline adventure takes you through the marvelous wonders of our rainforest. You will explore the Tarcoles River on our stunning pacific coast.</strong>\n\n<strong>Your guide will point out different kinds of mammals, birds and reptiles that flourish in this mangrove system. Depending on the season you will be able to spot different migratory aviary species; from October to April you can glimpse ospreys, gulls, terns cormorants, pelicans and frigates.There will be numerous opportunities to take incredible pictures during the trip.</strong>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Day 8</strong></span></h3>\n<span style=\"color: #008080;\"><strong> Air-conditioned transportation from Quepos/Manuel Antonio to Int’l Airport Juan Santamaria to catch your flight home.</strong></span>\n\n[gravityform id=\"2\" title=\"true\" description=\"false\" ajax=\"true\"]', '3 nights at Arenal Volcano, 4 nights at jaco Beach (8 Days/ 7 Nights)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '23968-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-08-31 20:34:24', '2015-08-31 20:34:24', '', '23968', 'http://www.mmexperiencecr.com/2015/08/31/23968-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
